1
00:00:10,067 --> 00:00:12,033
<i>So Manuel only went back
to Hazel</i>

2
00:00:12,167 --> 00:00:13,100
<i> because of the deal?</i>

3
00:00:13,567 --> 00:00:15,133
<i> And you agreed? Why?</i>

4
00:00:15,533 --> 00:00:20,233
<i>If I had stopped Manuel,
Coleen would've gone to jail.</i>

5
00:00:20,367 --> 00:00:22,033
<i>- Dad, answer...
- Don't. Don't.</i>

6
00:00:22,167 --> 00:00:23,333
<i>- What are you doing?
- Stop, stop, stop!</i>

7
00:00:23,467 --> 00:00:24,867
<i> Don't call Uncle Manuel.</i>

8
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:26,433
<i> Hazel might catch him.</i>

9
00:00:26,567 --> 00:00:28,800
<i>Better wait for him
to call you instead.</i>

10
00:00:29,767 --> 00:00:30,367
<i> Didang!</i>

11
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:32,100
<i> Pork adobo? Why?</i>

12
00:00:32,233 --> 00:00:35,467
<i>Ma'am, you're too young to be
forgetting things, right?</i>

13
00:00:35,633 --> 00:00:37,833
<i>You really told me
to cook pork adobo.</i>

14
00:00:37,967 --> 00:00:38,967
<i> I even asked you, Ma'am.</i>

15
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:40,467
<i> So you're saying...</i>

16
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:42,867
<i> I'm lying?</i>

17
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:50,767
Ma'am, you really asked me
to cook pork adobo.

18
00:00:50,900 --> 00:00:51,700
I swear.

19
00:00:51,833 --> 00:00:55,733
No! I told you to cook
chicken adobo!

20
00:00:56,100 --> 00:00:59,867
Don't make me look like a liar
in front of my kids!

21
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:01,400
- Ma'am, but...
- What?

22
00:01:01,533 --> 00:01:02,567
You're still insisting?

23
00:01:02,700 --> 00:01:04,133
Mom, Mom, Mom...

24
00:01:04,267 --> 00:01:06,767
Mom, whether it's chicken
or pork, it's still adobo.

25
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:08,300
No, Jeffrey!

26
00:01:08,467 --> 00:01:10,300
Didang has no respect!

27
00:01:10,433 --> 00:01:11,700
She doesn't listen!

28
00:01:11,833 --> 00:01:13,533
What, you think
you can play with me?

29
00:01:14,100 --> 00:01:15,100
Ma'am,

30
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:17,700
how did this even turn into
a conversation about respect,

31
00:01:17,833 --> 00:01:18,767
about the adobo?

32
00:01:18,900 --> 00:01:20,433
- Oh, you're answering back now?
- Mom, stop...

33
00:01:20,567 --> 00:01:23,133
- Talking back now?
- Mom, Mom, stop.

34
00:01:23,267 --> 00:01:26,033
- Felma, Felma.
- She's getting out of line!

35
00:01:26,167 --> 00:01:27,633
No respect!

36
00:01:27,767 --> 00:01:29,000
- What?
- Enough, enough.

37
00:01:29,133 --> 00:01:30,433
Let's go outside, get some air.

38
00:01:30,567 --> 00:01:32,067
You're too much, Didang!

39
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:33,867
Come on, let's get some air.

40
00:01:42,133 --> 00:01:43,400
What happened to Mom?

41
00:01:44,767 --> 00:01:46,633
I know, she's...

42
00:01:46,767 --> 00:01:48,267
She's been acting weird.

43
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:51,067
We've been noticing it.

44
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,667
Right, Didang?

45
00:02:09,533 --> 00:02:10,833
Sis.

46
00:02:12,333 --> 00:02:13,567
Didang!

47
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:14,833
Oh, Jeffrey.

48
00:02:15,567 --> 00:02:17,500
Jeffrey, did Uncle Manuel
text you yet?

49
00:02:17,633 --> 00:02:18,667
I haven't checked.

50
00:02:20,533 --> 00:02:21,533
He did.

51
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:26,733
<i> Son, sorry I didn't answer.</i>

52
00:02:26,867 --> 00:02:29,200
<i> Hazel almost caught me.</i>

53
00:02:29,333 --> 00:02:30,933
<i> Don't call, okay?</i>

54
00:02:31,067 --> 00:02:34,467
<i>Wait for me to call or text you.</i>

55
00:02:51,133 --> 00:02:54,400
- Didang?
- Didang.

56
00:02:54,533 --> 00:02:57,200
Didang, please stop crying.

57
00:02:57,333 --> 00:03:01,567
You know, Coleen, that's easy
for you to say.

58
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:05,867
Because you weren't the one
who got yelled at.

59
00:03:06,367 --> 00:03:08,567
You weren't the one embarrassed.

60
00:03:08,700 --> 00:03:11,000
You weren't the one hurt,

61
00:03:11,133 --> 00:03:14,667
like your soul
was stripped bare.

62
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,600
It wasn't you.

63
00:03:16,733 --> 00:03:18,700
Didang...

64
00:03:18,833 --> 00:03:20,367
Didang, we get you.

65
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:22,133
We know you're hurt.

66
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:23,333
No.

67
00:03:23,467 --> 00:03:25,133
No, you don't, Andrea.

68
00:03:25,267 --> 00:03:26,800
You don't know how it feels.

69
00:03:26,933 --> 00:03:31,500
After serving your family for
more than ten years...

70
00:03:32,967 --> 00:03:36,667
I treated you like
my own family.

71
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:38,333
But this...

72
00:03:38,467 --> 00:03:41,567
this is the first time
Ma'am Felma yelled at me.

73
00:03:46,333 --> 00:03:48,067
It hurts!

74
00:03:50,967 --> 00:03:52,967
It hurts so much!

75
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:55,533
I can't take the pain!

76
00:03:58,867 --> 00:04:02,233
Didang, Didang, promise

77
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:06,733
promise, we really do
understand you.

78
00:04:06,867 --> 00:04:07,933
But...

79
00:04:08,067 --> 00:04:11,667
maybe you can try
to understand Mom, too?

80
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:14,700
You know she's going through
something right now.

81
00:04:14,833 --> 00:04:15,633
What about me?

82
00:04:15,767 --> 00:04:17,433
Am I not going through anything?

83
00:04:17,567 --> 00:04:18,800
You, Coleen?

84
00:04:18,933 --> 00:04:22,000
You? You, too, Andrea?

85
00:04:22,133 --> 00:04:24,767
Didn't we all get hurt?

86
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:28,033
Didn't Sir Manuel
hurt all of us?

87
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:34,500
It hurts so much
that Sir Manuel left us!

88
00:04:36,533 --> 00:04:39,367
It hurts so much!

89
00:04:54,533 --> 00:04:56,733
Friend, are you okay?

90
00:04:56,867 --> 00:04:58,067
What happened?

91
00:05:00,167 --> 00:05:01,100
Alice...

92
00:05:03,300 --> 00:05:05,800
Manuel's so hard to deal with.

93
00:05:06,967 --> 00:05:08,367
And?

94
00:05:09,833 --> 00:05:11,267
And?

95
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:12,633
And what?

96
00:05:12,767 --> 00:05:13,967
That's it?

97
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:16,433
My god, Hazel.

98
00:05:16,567 --> 00:05:19,300
It's my day off,
I even had a date.

99
00:05:19,433 --> 00:05:21,700
I left it, even though
I was still annoyed at you

100
00:05:21,833 --> 00:05:25,067
from last time because your text
said it was an emergency.

101
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:28,600
And now you're just telling me
Manuel's hard to deal with?

102
00:05:28,733 --> 00:05:31,067
You're so inconsiderate.

103
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:32,433
I'm sorry.

104
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:36,000
I just needed someone
to vent to.

105
00:05:40,367 --> 00:05:42,400
You wanted this, right?

106
00:05:43,133 --> 00:05:45,167
You wanted to be
Mrs. Cruz again?

107
00:05:45,300 --> 00:05:47,067
Then own it.

108
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:48,233
How?

109
00:05:49,467 --> 00:05:50,767
What do I do?

110
00:05:51,633 --> 00:05:53,733
Manuel still hasn't
warmed up to me.

111
00:05:53,867 --> 00:05:55,333
Then endure it.

112
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:57,767
Come on, Alice.

113
00:05:58,933 --> 00:06:00,467
Please take me seriously.

114
00:06:01,867 --> 00:06:03,733
I need a friend right now.

115
00:06:07,033 --> 00:06:08,333
I'm serious, Hazel.

116
00:06:09,700 --> 00:06:14,500
If you want to win Manuel back,
endure it.

117
00:06:14,633 --> 00:06:15,733
Be patient.

118
00:06:16,700 --> 00:06:20,167
He's not the same Manuel
you used to push around before.

119
00:06:21,667 --> 00:06:23,767
And if you can't do that,

120
00:06:23,900 --> 00:06:25,300
then let him go.

121
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:28,400
No.

122
00:06:29,467 --> 00:06:31,967
I cannot afford
to let Manuel go.

123
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:34,867
I love him.

124
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,033
He's all I have.

125
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:43,100
Then there.

126
00:06:43,233 --> 00:06:44,667
Then follow my advice.

127
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,233
You're right.

128
00:06:49,767 --> 00:06:51,367
I'll endure it.

129
00:06:53,100 --> 00:06:54,067
I'll do everything,

130
00:06:55,333 --> 00:06:56,433
even if it's hard.

131
00:06:57,900 --> 00:06:59,733
Until he loves me again.

132
00:06:59,867 --> 00:07:01,633
I won't give up on Manuel.

133
00:07:03,100 --> 00:07:09,033
I'll stand my ground
as Mrs. Cruz.

134
00:07:19,367 --> 00:07:22,433
Uncle, you knew what Mom
and Dad's agreement was?

135
00:07:23,633 --> 00:07:25,167
Yes, she told me.

136
00:07:25,567 --> 00:07:26,400
What?

137
00:07:29,033 --> 00:07:30,700
Was she drunk when she told you?

138
00:07:32,067 --> 00:07:33,033
No, she wasn't.

139
00:07:34,533 --> 00:07:36,433
Even I was surprised.

140
00:07:36,567 --> 00:07:39,633
I didn't expect her
to open up to me

141
00:07:39,767 --> 00:07:41,933
about her problems with Manuel.

142
00:07:44,367 --> 00:07:48,100
You know, after everything
that happened between us,

143
00:07:48,267 --> 00:07:49,700
that is too personal.

144
00:07:49,967 --> 00:07:51,100
Exactly, Uncle.

145
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:53,200
That was supposed
to be a secret.

146
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:55,033
Why... why did she tell you?

147
00:07:55,167 --> 00:07:57,500
What? That was a secret?

148
00:07:57,633 --> 00:07:58,967
Then why did you tell me?

149
00:08:00,733 --> 00:08:01,900
Mine was different.

150
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:05,433
That day, I didn't know
what to do, I was a mess.

151
00:08:05,567 --> 00:08:07,967
I needed someone to talk to.

152
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:09,600
Maybe your mom felt
the same, Jeff.

153
00:08:10,933 --> 00:08:12,800
She's confused and angry.

154
00:08:12,933 --> 00:08:15,200
The burden she's carrying
is so heavy

155
00:08:15,333 --> 00:08:17,500
that she needs someone
to confide in.

156
00:08:18,633 --> 00:08:20,700
Good thing she told me.

157
00:08:20,867 --> 00:08:24,333
Son, better that than keeping it
in until she suddenly explodes.

158
00:08:25,567 --> 00:08:26,733
You're right, Uncle.

159
00:08:29,133 --> 00:08:32,433
And you're one of the people
Mom trusts.

160
00:08:32,567 --> 00:08:34,033
I guess it's fine.

161
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:36,333
Yes, I really wanna help.

162
00:08:37,433 --> 00:08:38,700
In any way I can.

163
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:40,600
Not just Felma,

164
00:08:40,733 --> 00:08:42,600
but your whole family, Son.

165
00:08:44,267 --> 00:08:45,933
Uncle, thank you.

166
00:08:47,533 --> 00:08:49,400
But you know what I don't get?

167
00:08:49,533 --> 00:08:50,900
If she already told you...

168
00:08:52,033 --> 00:08:54,367
why did she explode at Didang

169
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:56,500
over something so tiny?

170
00:08:56,667 --> 00:08:58,167
Oh, I really don't know.

171
00:08:59,467 --> 00:09:00,667
What are you talking about?

172
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:01,833
It's about you, Auntie.

173
00:09:01,967 --> 00:09:04,400
Me? Why?

174
00:09:04,533 --> 00:09:05,967
Oh...

175
00:09:06,100 --> 00:09:07,533
We're just worried, Felma.

176
00:09:07,667 --> 00:09:08,900
Maybe you and Didang
aren't okay yet.

177
00:09:09,033 --> 00:09:11,567
- Oh.
- We're fine.

178
00:09:11,700 --> 00:09:14,233
I already apologized to her.

179
00:09:23,033 --> 00:09:25,900
Manuel, do you want me to
massage your feet

180
00:09:26,033 --> 00:09:27,300
before you sleep?

181
00:09:27,433 --> 00:09:28,467
No, don't.

182
00:09:29,933 --> 00:09:31,900
Come on, just a bit.

183
00:09:32,033 --> 00:09:35,133
You don't have an appointment
with your therapist yet,

184
00:09:35,267 --> 00:09:36,800
so I'll massage you for now,
give them to me.

185
00:09:36,933 --> 00:09:39,100
No, I said I'm fine, go on.

186
00:09:44,900 --> 00:09:48,833
All right, I'll finish
my transcription outside.

187
00:09:48,967 --> 00:09:51,700
If you need anything,
just call me, okay?

188
00:09:51,833 --> 00:09:53,433
I don't need anything from you.

189
00:09:56,100 --> 00:09:57,567
You know, if there's any,

190
00:09:57,700 --> 00:10:01,000
it's our deal,
Timo taking back his statement.

191
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:06,800
<i>If you want to win
Manuel back, endure it.</i>

192
00:10:06,933 --> 00:10:08,300
<i> Be patient.</i>

193
00:10:08,433 --> 00:10:11,800
<i>If you can't,
then let him go.</i>

194
00:10:31,867 --> 00:10:35,367
<i>Jeffrey, son,
how are you all?</i>

195
00:10:35,533 --> 00:10:37,167
<i> I miss you all so much.</i>

196
00:10:37,300 --> 00:10:39,533
<i> Especially your mom.</i>

197
00:10:39,667 --> 00:10:41,800
<i>Take care of them for me, okay?</i>

198
00:10:41,933 --> 00:10:43,833
<i> I love you.</i>

199
00:10:43,967 --> 00:10:45,467
<i> Love you all so much.</i>

200
00:10:48,733 --> 00:10:50,367
Mom, look.

201
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:52,900
Dad texted,
he said he misses us a lot.

202
00:10:57,367 --> 00:10:58,700
I guess this is better, Mom.

203
00:11:00,033 --> 00:11:02,567
At least now we can text, right?

204
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:06,833
Not like when we were kids,
no communication at all.

205
00:11:09,067 --> 00:11:11,100
All we can do is text.

206
00:11:12,700 --> 00:11:14,567
At least, Mom, he hasn't
forgotten us, right?

207
00:11:16,100 --> 00:11:20,300
I'm sure if Dad
had the chance, he'd call.

208
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:26,467
It's just hard.

209
00:11:28,467 --> 00:11:30,133
He's so close.

210
00:11:31,433 --> 00:11:32,733
He's not even abroad.

211
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:37,533
But it feels like
he's so far away.

212
00:11:41,700 --> 00:11:42,633
Mom, why?

213
00:11:43,733 --> 00:11:46,133
- Oh...
- Mom?

214
00:11:46,833 --> 00:11:48,300
Oh...

215
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:51,433
My head just hurts.

216
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:54,933
Maybe you're just tired
from today, Mom.

217
00:11:55,067 --> 00:11:57,133
You should rest, Mom.

218
00:11:57,267 --> 00:11:57,967
All right, son.

219
00:11:58,967 --> 00:12:00,467
- Thank you.
- Go, rest now.

220
00:12:19,167 --> 00:12:20,700
Coleen.

221
00:12:20,833 --> 00:12:22,167
Sweetie.

222
00:12:22,300 --> 00:12:24,733
- Oh?
- Sweetie, wake up.

223
00:12:24,867 --> 00:12:27,533
Come on, Coleen.

224
00:12:27,667 --> 00:12:31,167
We already had breakfast,
you're still asleep.

225
00:12:31,300 --> 00:12:32,967
Get up, It's already noon.

226
00:12:33,100 --> 00:12:35,567
Sis, five minutes.

227
00:12:35,700 --> 00:12:37,133
Coleen, please, come on.

228
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:42,267
Sis, why?

229
00:12:43,467 --> 00:12:47,133
Do we have something important
to do or go to?

230
00:12:47,267 --> 00:12:49,000
We don't, right?

231
00:12:49,167 --> 00:12:51,967
But you can't just stay here
in bed all day.

232
00:12:52,700 --> 00:12:54,600
Why not?

233
00:12:55,100 --> 00:12:57,133
I'd rather just sleep.

234
00:12:58,567 --> 00:13:02,300
Because when I'm awake,
I remember the hearing.

235
00:13:02,433 --> 00:13:05,267
And I remember Dad's
not here anymore.

236
00:13:06,733 --> 00:13:08,300
And Mom...

237
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:11,333
Andrea, until now,
I still don't understand

238
00:13:11,467 --> 00:13:15,400
why Mom agreed so fast
to let Dad leave.

239
00:13:23,167 --> 00:13:24,133
Do you want us

240
00:13:25,967 --> 00:13:28,967
to visit
your psychologist again?

241
00:13:29,100 --> 00:13:32,567
Maybe talking
to Doctor Darla might help.

242
00:13:32,700 --> 00:13:35,733
She'll just prescribe
calming meds again.

243
00:13:37,467 --> 00:13:39,200
So what can we do?

244
00:13:39,667 --> 00:13:43,367
It should be something
that'll make you happy.

245
00:13:44,533 --> 00:13:46,400
Ah! I know!

246
00:13:46,533 --> 00:13:47,433
Baking?

247
00:13:47,567 --> 00:13:48,933
Let's bake, you teach me.

248
00:13:49,067 --> 00:13:51,467
- Come on.
- Sis, I'm not in the mood.

249
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:54,767
Dear, you need to make better
use of your time.

250
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:57,833
Me, too.

251
00:13:58,900 --> 00:14:02,233
Of course, I'm affected by
what happened to our family.

252
00:14:02,733 --> 00:14:06,167
But I'm trying to find ways
to cope.

253
00:14:08,433 --> 00:14:10,300
Dear, I hope you do the same.

254
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,733
We can get through this.

255
00:14:17,233 --> 00:14:19,300
As long as we're together.

256
00:14:20,267 --> 00:14:21,833
Okay, Andrea.

257
00:14:21,967 --> 00:14:23,333
I'll shower first.

258
00:14:23,767 --> 00:14:24,733
Promise?

259
00:14:24,867 --> 00:14:26,633
I'll wait for you downstairs.

260
00:14:26,767 --> 00:14:28,567
Oh?

261
00:14:28,733 --> 00:14:29,800
I'll wait for you downstairs.

262
00:14:29,933 --> 00:14:31,133
Oh....

263
00:14:53,167 --> 00:14:55,000
Oh, Manuel, where are you going?

264
00:14:56,367 --> 00:14:58,233
To the garden,
Is that not allowed?

265
00:14:59,267 --> 00:15:00,433
It's not that.

266
00:15:00,567 --> 00:15:02,100
It's your tone.

267
00:15:02,267 --> 00:15:04,600
It's like you want me to report
every move I make.

268
00:15:04,733 --> 00:15:07,000
Just tell me if you want
to chain me up.

269
00:15:08,067 --> 00:15:09,033
Come on, Manuel.

270
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:11,733
Why are you upset right away?

271
00:15:12,267 --> 00:15:14,300
I'm not that kind of person.

272
00:15:14,433 --> 00:15:17,433
I just thought
you might need my help.

273
00:15:18,367 --> 00:15:19,867
No.

274
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,667
Especially not from you.

275
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:33,100
Hello, Miss Magcaling?

276
00:15:33,233 --> 00:15:35,200
Yes, we're ready.

277
00:15:35,367 --> 00:15:38,067
The products will be there
by Thursday,

278
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:40,333
In time for the opening
of your store.

279
00:15:40,467 --> 00:15:41,600
Yes.

280
00:15:41,733 --> 00:15:43,467
Yes, thank you,
see you.

281
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:48,667
Okay, that's settled, bye.

282
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:49,800
Andrea.

283
00:15:49,933 --> 00:15:50,767
Andrea, I passed by the eatery.

284
00:15:50,900 --> 00:15:51,767
Thought you might not have had a
snack yet.

285
00:15:52,767 --> 00:15:53,433
Ah...

286
00:15:53,900 --> 00:15:57,500
- Thank you, what is this?
- I hope you like it.

287
00:15:58,633 --> 00:16:01,133
Oh?

288
00:16:01,267 --> 00:16:03,567
- Barbecue.
- Yes, barbecue.

289
00:16:03,700 --> 00:16:05,933
<i> Remember when you were little?</i>

290
00:16:06,067 --> 00:16:09,233
<i>Whenever I grilled,
you always wanted to help.</i>

291
00:16:09,400 --> 00:16:11,300
<i> But I never let you.</i>

292
00:16:11,533 --> 00:16:13,767
<i>Because I always burned things.</i>

293
00:16:17,400 --> 00:16:18,400
Why?

294
00:16:28,267 --> 00:16:30,033
Where are you going?

295
00:16:30,167 --> 00:16:32,133
We're going, come on.

296
00:16:39,733 --> 00:16:41,067
Whose house is this?

297
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:48,567
I've been asking you.

298
00:16:48,700 --> 00:16:49,433
You won't answer.

299
00:16:49,567 --> 00:16:51,133
Why?

300
00:16:55,100 --> 00:16:56,533
I'm afraid you'll stop me.

301
00:17:05,633 --> 00:17:06,667
Who is it?

302
00:17:08,533 --> 00:17:09,767
What are you doing here?

303
00:17:10,867 --> 00:17:11,700
Is Dad here?

304
00:17:11,833 --> 00:17:13,333
Can I talk to him?

305
00:17:13,467 --> 00:17:15,067
He's resting.

306
00:17:15,233 --> 00:17:17,433
Please tell him I'm here.

307
00:17:17,567 --> 00:17:21,567
I'm sure he'll talk to me
if he knows.

308
00:17:21,700 --> 00:17:23,067
Sorry.

309
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:24,600
- Hazel.
- Andrea.

310
00:17:24,733 --> 00:17:25,900
Please.

311
00:17:26,033 --> 00:17:27,000
Just for a moment.

312
00:17:28,300 --> 00:17:30,067
I said he can't.

313
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:31,400
He's already asleep.

314
00:17:31,533 --> 00:17:33,967
Come on,
take her home.

315
00:17:34,100 --> 00:17:35,300
Come on, let's go.

316
00:17:35,433 --> 00:17:36,467
Leave now!

317
00:17:40,867 --> 00:17:41,800
- Oh!
- Andrea!

318
00:17:41,933 --> 00:17:43,033
- Dad? Dad?
- Andrea!

319
00:17:43,167 --> 00:17:44,200
- Dad?
- Andrea!

320
00:17:44,333 --> 00:17:45,800
Andrea.

321
00:17:45,933 --> 00:17:47,667
- Dad!
- Come here!

322
00:17:52,733 --> 00:17:54,767
Dad, why did you leave us?

323
00:17:58,567 --> 00:18:00,200
Dad...

324
00:18:00,333 --> 00:18:02,300
you didn't even
say goodbye.

325
00:18:03,700 --> 00:18:06,033
You just disappeared.

326
00:18:06,167 --> 00:18:09,100
And then we found out
you went back to Hazel?

327
00:18:11,567 --> 00:18:14,333
Dad, you made
a promise to me...

328
00:18:14,833 --> 00:18:17,167
remember?

329
00:18:17,300 --> 00:18:18,700
<i> I'll make it up to you.</i>

330
00:18:18,833 --> 00:18:20,867
<i> I'll fix all my mistakes.</i>

331
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:22,600
<i> Thank you, Dad.</i>

332
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:25,933
<i>Thank you for coming back to us.</i>

333
00:18:28,067 --> 00:18:30,000
But what happened now?

334
00:18:30,133 --> 00:18:32,300
It feels like you're doing
the same thing you did

335
00:18:32,433 --> 00:18:34,567
when we were kids.

336
00:18:34,700 --> 00:18:38,167
You promised you'd
never leave me again,

337
00:18:38,300 --> 00:18:40,033
that you'd never leave us again.

338
00:18:41,267 --> 00:18:42,933
But you broke
that promise again.

339
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:47,233
Andrea.

340
00:18:49,067 --> 00:18:50,367
Andrea, I'm sorry I hurt you.

341
00:18:50,500 --> 00:18:51,767
But...

342
00:18:51,900 --> 00:18:54,300
I also made a promise
to Jessica.

343
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:57,467
And I have to keep that.

344
00:19:05,133 --> 00:19:06,000
Oh, Felma...

345
00:19:06,133 --> 00:19:08,533
I brought you some lavender tea.

346
00:19:08,667 --> 00:19:10,533
Should I make it for you?

347
00:19:10,667 --> 00:19:12,600
Let Didang do it.

348
00:19:12,733 --> 00:19:14,300
Oh, thank you.

349
00:19:14,433 --> 00:19:16,200
I'm bothering you too much.

350
00:19:17,367 --> 00:19:18,967
Come on.

351
00:19:19,100 --> 00:19:20,767
Felma, of course not.

352
00:19:20,900 --> 00:19:22,933
I like what I do.

353
00:19:23,067 --> 00:19:25,433
It feels embarrassing, but...

354
00:19:25,567 --> 00:19:27,367
let me take advantage
of your help for now.

355
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:32,767
I hope you can come
to Coleen's hearing.

356
00:19:34,333 --> 00:19:35,533
Of course.

357
00:19:35,667 --> 00:19:38,400
Actually, I already talked
to Arjun.

358
00:19:38,533 --> 00:19:40,167
I moved my schedules

359
00:19:40,300 --> 00:19:44,233
and asked the Davao group
to do the meetings online.

360
00:19:53,900 --> 00:19:54,967
Thank you.

361
00:19:55,100 --> 00:19:57,600
Your support means a lot,

362
00:19:57,733 --> 00:20:00,367
especially since Manuel
isn't with us.

363
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:07,700
Have you and Manuel talked?

364
00:20:08,333 --> 00:20:10,967
What's your setup during
the hearing?

365
00:20:11,100 --> 00:20:14,667
We can't just talk freely.

366
00:20:16,100 --> 00:20:18,667
That's what Hazel
and I agreed on.

367
00:20:22,033 --> 00:20:24,100
You made a promise to Jessica?

368
00:20:24,233 --> 00:20:25,767
What is it?

369
00:20:25,900 --> 00:20:27,833
To take care of her mom?

370
00:20:33,767 --> 00:20:35,933
So that's why you told us...

371
00:20:37,367 --> 00:20:39,633
we needed to learn
to stand on our own.

372
00:20:39,767 --> 00:20:42,367
<i>What you can learn now,
learn it.</i>

373
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:44,333
<i> Don't rely on me.</i>

374
00:20:44,467 --> 00:20:48,167
<i>So when we get separated,
you can manage.</i>

375
00:20:49,767 --> 00:20:53,600
Turns out you were preparing us
for your leaving.

376
00:20:55,133 --> 00:20:57,433
Because you already knew
you'd leave us again.

377
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:01,433
But I don't get it, Dad.

378
00:21:02,600 --> 00:21:07,400
You were so sure that we'd be
one whole family again.

379
00:21:09,367 --> 00:21:10,500
Right?

380
00:21:10,633 --> 00:21:13,100
If you really had
to take care of Hazel,

381
00:21:13,233 --> 00:21:16,500
you could do that
without leaving us.

382
00:21:16,633 --> 00:21:18,733
Check on her from time to time.

383
00:21:18,867 --> 00:21:19,733
Call her.

384
00:21:19,867 --> 00:21:22,400
If needed, visit her, huh?

385
00:21:22,533 --> 00:21:24,033
- Wait a second, Andrea...
- What wait?

386
00:21:28,967 --> 00:21:30,267
Dad, Jessica is gone.

387
00:21:31,367 --> 00:21:34,100
But Jeff, Coleen,
and I are still here.

388
00:21:35,133 --> 00:21:36,900
We're so alive.

389
00:21:37,033 --> 00:21:38,500
We need a father.

390
00:21:42,900 --> 00:21:44,467
Wait, Andrea.

391
00:21:45,133 --> 00:21:47,533
Just because Jessica is gone

392
00:21:47,667 --> 00:21:49,667
doesn't mean she stopped being
Manuel's daughter.

393
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:51,633
And it's the same for Manuel.

394
00:21:51,767 --> 00:21:53,833
He's still Jessica's dad.

395
00:21:53,967 --> 00:21:56,600
And as long
as I'm Manuel's wife,

396
00:21:56,733 --> 00:21:58,967
he remains Jessica's father.

397
00:21:59,100 --> 00:22:00,633
Hazel!

398
00:22:00,767 --> 00:22:01,833
Hold on, Manuel.

399
00:22:02,733 --> 00:22:04,700
I'm confused.

400
00:22:04,833 --> 00:22:06,400
Why, Andrea?

401
00:22:06,533 --> 00:22:07,833
What did your mother tell you?

402
00:22:10,367 --> 00:22:11,467
Don't you two talk?

403
00:22:12,600 --> 00:22:13,567
Why?

404
00:22:14,900 --> 00:22:16,967
What exactly should
we be talking about?

405
00:22:18,033 --> 00:22:19,967
That you were hurting yourself?

406
00:22:20,100 --> 00:22:22,267
That's why Dad had
to take care of you?

407
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:24,033
That he had to come back to you?

408
00:22:25,700 --> 00:22:27,600
Is that what they told you?

409
00:22:28,300 --> 00:22:30,600
And you believed that?

410
00:22:32,167 --> 00:22:33,567
What?

411
00:22:34,700 --> 00:22:35,667
Why?

412
00:22:36,900 --> 00:22:38,433
Dad, what's going on?

413
00:22:46,900 --> 00:22:49,367
I hurt Andeng's
feelings earlier.

414
00:22:49,533 --> 00:22:50,633
How is she now?

415
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:54,333
Who's that?

416
00:22:57,367 --> 00:22:59,100
What was that?

417
00:22:59,233 --> 00:23:00,000
Oh my, Jeff.

418
00:23:00,133 --> 00:23:01,800
we need help,
It's your mom.

419
00:23:01,933 --> 00:23:03,567
Mom, come on,
please stop that.

420
00:23:03,700 --> 00:23:04,633
- Cheers.
- Mom!

421
00:23:04,767 --> 00:23:08,700
- Mom!
- Mom!

422
00:23:08,833 --> 00:23:11,700
Attorney, I asked you to come

423
00:23:11,833 --> 00:23:14,567
because I have to tell you
the truth.

424
00:23:15,633 --> 00:23:16,900
The truth?

425
00:23:17,033 --> 00:23:20,833
Coleen didn't push Jessica.
